text: St. Donatus is a city in Iowa in the United States. ==Name== The city of St. Donatus is named after Saint Donatus of Muenstereifel. It used to be called Tetes de Morts, which is the name of a creek that flows through the town. ==Location== The geographic coordinates of St. Donatus are (42.360590, -90.538790). St. Donatus is in Jackson County, Iowa. ==Statistics== The United States Census Bureau says that the city's land takes up . In the year 2020, the census showed that there were 120 people living in St. Donatus. These people lived in 54 households. In 2021, the median household earned about $36,838 each year. ==References== Category:Cities in Iowa
